ot;EN-US\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" b=\\"\\" unity=\\"\\" within=\\"\\" other=\\"\\" progressive=\\"\\" movements=\\"\\" campaigns=\\"\\" alliance=\\"\\" key=\\"\\" player=\\"\\" meeting=\\"\\" of=\\"\\" left=\\"\\" community=\\"\\" local=\\"\\" parties=\\"\\" organizations=\\"\\" which=\\"\\" held=\\"\\" rugby=\\"\\" july.=\\"\\" idea=\\"\\" originated=\\"\\" former=\\"\\" sa=\\"\\" member=\\"\\" nick=\\"\\" long=\\"\\" who=\\"\\" asked=\\"\\" come=\\"\\" on=\\"\\" board=\\"\\" met=\\"\\" up=\\"\\" with=\\"\\" pete=\\"\\" mclaren=\\"\\" help=\\"\\" him=\\"\\" organise=\\"\\" this=\\"\\" meeting.span=\\"\\" spanthe=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" endorsed=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" by=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" for=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" green=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" socialism,=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" red=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" alliance,=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" liaison=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" committee,=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" wellingborough=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" socialists,=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" barrow=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" peoples=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" lewisham=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" people=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" before=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" profit.span=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" /spanIt was agreed to invite all locally\r\nregistered left/green-left/progressive political parties â€“ including the\r\nKidderminster Health Concern, Cambridge Socialists, Wigan Community Action, span style=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;color:black\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"Walsall DLP,/span radical groups from Preston, Manchester\r\nand Northampton, and the Oxford based Independent Working Class Association as\r\nwell as those who had already endorsed the Meeting as listed above.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" yes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" spanit=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" was=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\" also=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;');
INSERT INTO `sublinks` (`sublinkid`, `sublinkname`, `sublinkorder`, `linkid`, `content`) VALUES
(84, 'National Shop stewards Network agrees to launch an \\"anti-cuts campaign, bringing trade unions and communities together to save all jobs and services', 4, 1, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-bottom:17.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:16.0pt;font-family:\\" arial-boldmt;mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><b>REPORT FROM THE NSSN CONFERENCE\r\n22/01/11</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-bottom:13.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\">Nearly 600 people met on Saturday 22 January for the special anti-cuts\r\nconference of the National Shop Stewards Network (NSSN).<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanbThe Conference debated two motions â€“\r\nboth are printed overleaf.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span></b></span><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Motion one\\'', from\r\na majority of the NSSN steering committee, proposed that the NSSN launches an \\"anti-cuts campaign, bringing trade unions and communities together to\r\nsave all jobs and services\\".</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-bottom:13.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\">Motion \\''two\\'', from a minority of the steering committee, proposed that\r\nthe NSSN should not launch an anti-cuts campaign, and instead should \\"do\r\neverything constructive, through discussions with Coalition of Resistance,\r\nRight to Work and other groups, to build and launch a single national anti-cuts\r\norganisation early in 2011\\" (see appendix for the two motions). <b>Two\r\nNSSN officers chaired the discussion, one from each side of the debate.</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-bottom:13.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\">In the vote after the debate, 305 trade union branch and workplace\r\nrepresentatives voted for motion one, against 89 for motion two (NB: nearly 200\r\nobservers and anti-cuts campaign representatives also attended the conference\r\nbut were not part of this vote, to respect the democratic structure of the\r\nNSSN).<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanA committee of eleven\r\npeople, six from trade unions and five from community anti-cuts campaigns, was then\r\nelected unopposed, to lead the NSSN\\''s new anti-cuts campaign â€“ it includes the\r\nSAâ€™s Toby Abse and independent socialist Terry Pearce./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-bottom:13.0pt;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"The proposers of Motion 1 made it clear that they will discuss with the\r\nother national anti-cuts organisations and explore the extent to which united\r\nwork can be achieved./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"The debate largely centered around the extent to which the anti cuts\r\nmovement should include Labour councilors who would be voting for cuts, and\r\nwhether the trade unions were ready to take on the government.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>Those supporting Motion 1, the majority\r\nposition, included the following points:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-top:0cm\\\\&quot;\\" type=\\"\\\\&quot;square\\\\&quot;\\">\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"We should\r\n  work with members of the Labour party opposed to cuts, but not with Labour\r\n  councilors who are imposing the cuts. /span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Labour\r\n  councils should refuse to pass on government cuts, as Liverpool and\r\n  Lambeth councils did in the 1980s.</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"There is a\r\n  need to co-ordinate anti cuts committees/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">The NSSN was\r\n  set up a long time before Right to Work (RtW) and Coalition of Resistance\r\n  (CoR)</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"If there was\r\n  an established national anti-cuts organisation in existence with a\r\n  strategy for defeating the cuts, then the NSSN wouldn\\\\\\''t need to be\r\n  proposing another one./span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Some of the\r\n  supporters of Motion 2 accept the need for some cuts</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l1\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"The Socialist\r\n  Party wants the leaders of all the anti-cuts campaigns to meet together to\r\n  discuss how the anti-cuts movement can be built./span/li\r\n/ul\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"Points in support of Motion 2 included the following:/span/p\r\n\r\nul style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-top:0cm\\\\&quot;\\" type=\\"\\\\&quot;square\\\\&quot;\\"\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Trade unions\r\n  are weaker today than in the 1980s, so the NSSN\\\\\\''s key task is to establish\r\n  the base for trade union resistance to the cuts.</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"The left\r\n  isn\\''t big enough to lead the anti-cuts movement/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">The role of\r\n  the NSSN is to continue to build workers\\\\\\'' solidarity and the shop\r\n  stewards\\\\\\'' movement.</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"We do not\r\n  want a SP dominated anti cuts movement where decisions are taken within\r\n  the SP not the NSSN/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">We can not\r\n  stop all the cuts</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"The NSSN\r\n  should work with RTW and the CoR/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:l2\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo2;=\\"\\" tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">The NSSN can\r\n  not set itself up as the leadership of the campaign against the cuts</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><b> </b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\">There were 30 contributions altogether in the debate, 15 for motion one\r\nand 15 for motion two. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:\\" en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><b>Appendix:</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" align=\\"\\\\&quot;center\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;text-align:center;mso-pagination:none;\\" mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bMotion 1/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"bANTI-CUTS CONFERENCE/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"The NSSN believes that, given the pace of attacks on\r\nliving standards by the ConDem government, it is now time to give form to our\r\ncommitment made at the June conference, to take our work \\\\\\"out to the wider\r\ncommunity\\"./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"We believe that the way to continue carrying out our\r\nfounding aim \\"to support trade unions in their campaigns and\r\ndisputes\\\\\\" is now clearly centered on the fight to STOP ALL CUTS whether\r\nthrough redundancy, reorganisation or privatisation./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"bWe believe that two sections are key to stopping\r\ncuts/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"1) Trade unions at local, regional and national level\r\n(and trades councils) with the potential power of 6 million organised workers,\r\nwho can organise mass strikes and coordinated joint action./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"2) Anti-cuts campaigns against cuts in services, and\r\nincluding students unions, tenants and pensioners organisations, welfare\r\nclaimants and disability groups, which can all initiate demonstrations,\r\noccupations and other direct action without being bound by legal ballots and other\r\nrestrictions (as shown graphically by the recent student events); or they can\r\norganise support to back up trade union actions to stop job cuts and save\r\nservices./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"bWe therefore propose to/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"a) Launch an \\\\\\"NSSN Anti-Cuts Campaign, bringing\r\ntrade unions and communities together to save all jobs and services\\\\\\"./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"b) Elect a committee of 10, comprised of 6 from trade\r\nunions and 4 from anti-cuts campaigns â€“ to be elected at the Conference â€“ plus\r\nNSSN Chair and Secretary./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"This committee could also co-opt pro-tem representatives\r\nfrom national/regional unions, and could respond quickly and flexibly to events\r\nas they unfold./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"bAmongst its first tasks would be assisting in/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-pagination:\\" none;mso-list:l0=\\"\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo3;tab-stops:11.0pt=\\"\\" list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:=\\"\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Wingdings;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Â§<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font:7.0pt\\" &quot;times=\\"\\" new=\\"\\" roman&quot;\\\\\\"=\\"\\"  /span/spanspan lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bRelentless\r\nlobbying of councils and councillors, and other bodies, to persuade them NOT to\r\nvote for cuts/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-pagination:\\" none;mso-list:l0=\\"\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo3;tab-stops:11.0pt=\\"\\" list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:=\\"\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Wingdings;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Â§<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font:7.0pt\\" &quot;times=\\"\\" new=\\"\\" roman&quot;\\\\\\"=\\"\\"  /span/spanspan lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bOrganise\r\na strong contingent for TUC demo in March/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-pagination:\\" none;mso-list:l0=\\"\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo3;tab-stops:11.0pt=\\"\\" list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:=\\"\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Wingdings;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Â§<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font:7.0pt\\" &quot;times=\\"\\" new=\\"\\" roman&quot;\\\\\\"=\\"\\"  /span/spanspan lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bCampaign\r\nfor united industrial action by the unions against the cuts/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-pagination:\\" none;mso-list:l0=\\"\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo3;tab-stops:11.0pt=\\"\\" list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:=\\"\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Wingdings;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Â§<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font:7.0pt\\" &quot;times=\\"\\" new=\\"\\" roman&quot;\\\\\\"=\\"\\"  /span/spanspan lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bProduce\r\na regular email organiser to assist and inform/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-pagination:\\" none;mso-list:l0=\\"\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo3;tab-stops:11.0pt=\\"\\" list=\\"\\" 36.0pt;mso-layout-grid-align:=\\"\\" none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Wingdings;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\">Â§<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font:7.0pt\\" &quot;times=\\"\\" new=\\"\\" roman&quot;\\\\\\"=\\"\\"  /span/spanspan lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bUse\r\nall forms of electronic communication including email, face book and the web\r\nsite to promote the anti cuts campaign/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" align=\\"\\\\&quot;center\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;text-align:center;mso-pagination:none;\\" mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;color:#FA1305;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" align=\\"\\\\&quot;center\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;text-align:center;mso-pagination:none;\\" mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"bMotion 2/b/span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"The NSSN calls upon all its trade union supporters and\r\naffiliates to ensure the largest possible turnout for our national anti-cuts\r\nconference on January 22nd./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"We re-affirm our commitment, as trades unionists, to\r\nwork to build and strengthen the local, regional and national anti-cuts\r\nmovement, between now and January 22nd./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"Given our basis as an industrial organisation, the\r\nJanuary Conference should concentrate on providing the widest possible debate\r\non the tactics and strategy needed to ensure that trade union strike action\r\nagainst the cuts begins sooner rather than later, that it is co-ordinated at\r\nlocal and national level, and that if possible it is sustained rather than\r\nrestricted to token efforts./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;\\" text-autospace:none\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"It follows from this that this conference should NOT\r\ndeclare the NSSN as THE lead organisation of a national anti-cuts movement:\r\nrather, that the NSSN Officers and Steering Committee do everything\r\nconstructive, through discussions with Coalition of Resistance, Right To Work\r\nand other groups, to build and launch a single national anti-cuts organisation\r\nearly in 2011./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\">Whilst Conference should allow time for a full and\r\nnecessary debate concerning trade union bodies supporting anti-cuts candidates\r\nin 2011 elections, the NSSN will leave decisions as to whether to stand such\r\ncandidates to our local and national affiliates.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Times;\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span></span><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-tab-count:1\\\\&quot;\\">   </span></span><span lang=\\"\\\\&quot;EN-US\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:Times;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\\\\&quot;\\"><i>Pete McLaren\r\n24/01/11</i></span><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Times\\\\&quot;\\"></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n'),
(83, 'TRADE UNIONIST AND SOCIALIST COALITION AGREES POLICIES TO FIGHT THE CUTS IN THE 2011 COUNCIL ELECTIONS', 3, 1, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"><b>Pete McLaren, SA National Secretary, reports from the TUSC Conference on January 22nd</b></p><p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"><i>Dave Nellist</i><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\"> opened\r\nthe Conference by expressing the need for hundreds of candidates in the May\r\nelections to fight the cuts and provide opposition to the BNP </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"><i>Michael Lavellette</i><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\">\r\n(SWP) spoke about his 9 years as a Socialist councillor in Preston.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanHe argued we must stand together\r\nagainst the cuts.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>Five Labour\r\ncouncillors had informed the local TUC they would oppose cuts only to vote for\r\ncuts in the Council vote.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanHe still\r\nthought we needed to find ways of working with those 60,000 new members of the\r\nLabour Party who had joined since the General Election./spani/i/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"iClive Heemskerk/ispan style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\" (SP)\r\ncalled for candidates rooted in the anti cuts movement.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>Councils were at the forefront of the\r\nstruggle, but, as the TUSC platform spelt out, then did not need to implement\r\ncuts.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanCouncils should set a â€œNeeds\r\nBudgetâ€ and demand the government makes up the rest, as Liverpool did in the\r\n1980â€™s.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>Surcharging was no longer\r\na major issue as it only now existed for individual fraud.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanAny Councillor accused of breaking the\r\nCode of Conduct, according to the Standards Board, would be entitled to a\r\nhearing, which itself would be a focus for mass protest, and at worst case\r\ncould only result in a 5 year ban from being a councillor!span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>Councillors should use reserves and\r\nprudential borrowing powers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"><i>Owen Herbert</i><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\"> (RMT)\r\napologised for arriving late.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanHe\r\noutlined how Labour had betrayed the working class and was now calling for\r\ncuts, but a slower pace.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>The\r\nresults were the same.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanIn Swansea,\r\nthe Labour Council had threatened to sack its workforce if they would not\r\naccept its cuts package and then re-instate workers on new inferior\r\nconditions.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>The Welsh TUC was\r\ndoing nothing, and a TUSC intervention was essential</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\">Alan from Darlington UNISON moved the one amendment to the\r\nplatform â€“ that council tax could be raised above inflation if approved by the\r\nelectorate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\">The platform was opened for discussion, and 22 individuals\r\nspoke â€“ 11 from the SP, 2 from the SA, 1 from SR, 3 from the SWP and 5\r\nindependents.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanPoints made included\r\nthe following;/p\r\n\r\nul style=\\"\\\\&quot;margin-top:0cm\\\\&quot;\\" type=\\"\\\\&quot;square\\\\&quot;\\"\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">We need to work with Labour Party members</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"There is no evidence of activism amongst the new\r\n  layer of Labour Party members/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">There should be national issues in the TUSC local\r\n  elections platform</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"There needs to be a new Party, and it should\r\n  champion democracy/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">There should be something on pay and conditions\r\n  within the TUSC platform</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"Candidates need to be involved in local campaigns/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">We need to build TUSC.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanThe fortnightly Bulletin should help.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span></span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"TUSC should stand in Barnsley to help establish\r\n  itself/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">The TUSC Steering Committee has agreed to there\r\n  being an Independent Socialist Network within TUSC to encourage\r\n  involvement from independent socialists</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"We should use the TUC Demo to publicise TUSC/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">We should oppose all cuts, rent and council tax\r\n  increases as they are all attacks on the working class</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"TUSC provides a political direction for the anti\r\n  cuts movement/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">Setting up a local anti cuts group can persuade\r\n  local trade union activists to come on board, and in the longer term this\r\n  could be a basis for a new workersâ€™ party</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"We should not include Labour councillors as part\r\n  of our campaign unless they are prepared to vote against cuts/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">TUSC should be opened up and become fully\r\n  democratic</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"We should work with all who oppose the cuts,\r\n  whatever their label/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">Green councillors do not vote against cuts in\r\n  Council meetings</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"TUSC should work with Labour councillors who do\r\n  vote against cuts whilst standing against those who donâ€™t/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">We should write to ask Labour candidates whether\r\n  they would vote against cuts</span></li>\r\n <li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\"We need to discuss our position on police cuts/span/li\r\n li class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\" style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-list:l0\\" level1=\\"\\" lfo1;tab-stops:list=\\"\\" 36.0pt\\\\\\"=\\"\\"><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-size:10.0pt\\\\&quot;\\">We should add our opposition to any attacks on\r\n  pay or conditions to our platform position</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\">In their replies, <i>Michael Lavalette</i><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\"> explained that all SWP members opposed all\r\ncuts.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanHe went on to argue there\r\nneeded to be a clear alternative to Labour, adding that if a Left Councillor\r\nwas elected it boosted workersâ€™ confidence.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span></span><i>Clive Heemskerk</i><span style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\">\r\nargued for as many TUSC candidates as possible, adding that â€˜Trade Unionist\r\n&amp; Socialists Against the Cutsâ€™ had also been registered.<span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\" /spanHe accepted that TUSC was a work in\r\nprogress./span/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"Following the debate, the amendment was withdrawn/p\r\n\r\np class=\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\"iDave Nellist/ispan style=\\"\\\\&quot;font-style:normal\\\\&quot;\\"\r\nconcluded proceedings by putting the proposed TUSC platform to the vote.span style=\\"\\\\&quot;mso-spacerun:\\" yes\\\\\\"=\\"\\"> </span>It was agreed unanimously.');
